claims:
8. A method for providing an abstractive summary of a source textual document, the method performed on a computer and comprising:
generating at an encoder an encoding for the source textual document;
using a contextual model of a decoder separated into the contextual model and a language model, extracting words from the source textual document using the encoding;
using the language model of the decoder, generating vectors paraphrasing the source textual document based on pre-training with a training dataset; and
generating the abstractive summary of the source textual document from the extracted words and the generated vectors for paraphrasing.

13. A non-transitory machine readable medium having stored thereon instructions for performing a method comprising machine executable code which when executed by at least one machine, causes the machine to:
generate at an encoder an encoding for the source textual document;
using a contextual model of a decoder separated into the contextual model and a language model, extract words from the source textual document using the encoding;
using the language model of the decoder, generate vectors paraphrasing the source textual document based on pre-training with a training dataset; and
generate the abstractive summary of the source textual document from the extracted words and the generated vectors for paraphrasing.
